      <abstract>
        <p>Correction of May 7 article on national security; Sec Lawrence Summers quoted in full</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Because of an editing error, an article last Sunday about national security issues truncated a comment from Treasury Secretary Lawrence H. Summers. As reported, Mr. Summers said it was a mistake to ''overemphasize the link between economic forces and future conflict'' because noneconomic forces also cause wars. But the main point of his comment was, ''When people are prosperous and hopeful, they don't look for men on horseback.''</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>Because of an editing error, an article last Sunday about national security issues truncated a comment from Treasury Secretary Lawrence H. Summers. As reported, Mr. Summers said it was a mistake to ''overemphasize the link between economic forces and future conflict'' because noneconomic forces also cause wars. But the main point of his comment was, ''When people are prosperous and hopeful, they don't look for men on horseback.''</p>
